#Diverticulitis Etiology: Fecal impaction into pseudodiverticula causing inflammation
#Diverticulitis  Presentation: Fever, nausea, most commonly LLQ pain, and peritonitis
#Diverticulitis Diagnostic Tests: CT scan is the best and most accurate test
#Diverticulitis Treatment: Antibiotics for the first attack; surgical resection if it recurs of perforates
#Diverticulitis Complications: Abscess formation. No #endoscopy due to risk of perforation
